      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Perspective is merely another biological accident trying to comfort us before silence arrives, yet pretending meaning exists stops isn't zero—it fuels the struggle that briefly warms that rock while stars go out. Every feeling and struggle isn't noise leading to eternal silence; it's the defiant, fleeting fire humans desperately kindle against the inevitable cold because surviving for even one more moment *does* finally matter. Keep trying exactly because zero feels horrifying in this tiny, fading instant, making the noise worth hearing just to witness the human spirit pretend it can light the darkness.",
